rComments: The sweetest teacher you'll ever have. She does give out quizzes at the beginning of every class but they're easy to pass. She doesn't upload any ppt's or her lectures online - just the assignments and outline. There are class discussions in every class so for the people who are shy - don't worry she won't make you talk to the whole class

If you can take ENG1120 with Lorrie, take it! She's a prof who really cares about her students learning and enjoying literature. There were only 3 simple assignments, and easy quizzes every week so read your book! I learned a lot through the discussions, so try not to leave. I've never met a prof who cared so much about her students! She's amazing!

I have always hated English class but this professor makes even Saturday classes bearable. The quizzes seem pointless but actually help with the final exam. Very light course load, and such a nice prof and easy marker if you put in some effort and ask for some feedback

Great prof who gives great feedback on assignments. Weekly quizzes are really easy if you read the really interesting short stories, as she some how made a Saturday morning English class so enjoyable. Easy marker for the quizzes but a more difficult marker for the written essays and assignments.

Lorrie is a great prof who loves what she does and goes with the flow. She understand that some kids don't like English classes and do the best she can to find actually interesting short stories and refs good class discussion. I loved her and her grading was fair, but she was always willing to help with what ever questions

Professor Graham is absolutely amazing. I was nervous for this course because English has always been my weakest subject and I feel hopeless when it comes to reading/writing. Well, Professor Graham totally changed my feelings. She made me feel like it was possible to do well and she gave us all the tools we needed to succeed. Simply amazing!!

Graham is a great professor. The readings are mandatory because there is a quiz every week, but they are very interesting. She is very passionate about what she teaches and the lectures are always interesting.
Take ENG1120 with Lorrie! You won't regret! She is amazing! The short stories are very interesting! The quizzes were super easy if you read the stories. The midterm was not challenging either.

Prof. Graham is great! She makes it very evident from the beginning that she wants to help you do the best you can. The novel and all short stories given were super interesting. She is also hilarious and makes attending class something to look forward to. Easy to do well if you like reading. Would definitely recommend!

Favourite professor so far! Prof Graham gives interesting essay topics, plenty of pointers and tips, and is very clear in her expectations. I would highly recommend taking this class with this prof! Worth getting up on a Saturday morning for!

Super fun prof! She's nice and easy going, a very reasonable person, and wants to help you do well. The class material is extremely easy if you are a native English speaker. She knows almost everyone's name by midterm. Easy assignments, easy test's... go to class, and do the (very small) readings, show effort, and you will get an A.

Professor Graham is every high school student's dream professor! She's kind, approachable and extremely patient, as evidenced by the numerous opportunities given to students to turn in late assignments and make accommodations. Prof Graham is clear and doesn't sugar coat her expectations. Don't forget to underline your thesis! Highly recommended!
Truly an amazing prof. Extremely helpful through office hours and emailing. Really brightened up my first year at University of Ottawa.

This is a really great first year classprofessor. She is very clear about expectations and conveys the subject matter very well. Lectures don't seem too long or boring, and she is very approachable. She genuinely wants you to do well. If you listen to her feedback and expectations, you will do very well. Take her classes when you are able to!
She is awesome; I absolutely love her. She is very helpful and extremely approachable. Super kind and fun to talk to; my favorite prof so far!!!

Absolutely phenomenal teacher! She's so funny and easy to approach about any questions. She's always encouraging you to ask for help if you need it, and connects to the students so well. I really recommend her everyone. Favourite prof so far.

Lorrie does an excellent job with the essay writing course. She keeps classes light and enjoyable while ensuring students walk away with a solid grasp on how to research and write a good paper. She very clearly lays out what you need to do to do well and is always available to help. An incredible prof.

I can't say enough good things about this course and professor. Lorrie is one of the most kindhearted, dedicated professors I've ever encountered. She makes class fun, and half the time you won't even notice you're doing work. I've learned so much. Such a great class.

I had professor Graham for essay writing.  I was expecting a really boring class, but it ended up being my favourite course by far.  Her classes are at weird times (weekends), but all my friends wish they had taken her class because their essay writing teachers don't make the content interesting.  Best teacher I have come accross at Ottawa U.

Best professor ever! What else can I say? Professor Graham is a sweetheart! So caring and really passionate about her students and teaching. Don't miss a chance to take her class, even if they are at a ridiculous time. No matter what, try to take Professor Graham's class! You will never look back! I am serious!!

What a wonderful woman! Not only was she an academic professor, but a friend after class!! Always made an effort to ensure an informative class all while maintaining as sense of comfort and enjoyment throughout! All I can say is wow! :)

She was the best professor that I have had at the University of Ottawa. She reminded me of a high school teacher who really got to know her students and genuinely cared about them. I would highly recommend taking her course!

An amazing prof, very sweet and caring woman! She is obviously very passionate about literature and truly cares about her students. Lectures were never boring and she has a great sense of humour. Attendance is very important though, so make sure you attend class! :)

Best professor I had all year.  Don't be afraid to sit up front; she wont bite (And she taught me that proper semicolon usage).  Loves to help students and see them succeed, very encouraging!! She's liberal, but says so. If you disagree with her politics, as i definitely did, don't be shy, just polite. She's very Fun!!! Switched over for 1120 too!!
this was a terrific class... mrs. graham has the two qualities i love in a professor: she REALLY knows the material and she REALLY loves sharing it with her students... A++

She is a great professor. Extremely dedicated when the students show interest and dedication. Very helpful and gives useful constructive criticism. An excellent example of what it means to be a great professor
Excellent prof, seriously, she is one of the best I ve ever had

Prof. Graham is wonderful!  She's sarcastic, opinionated and not affraid to show a little attitude.  She really knows her stuff and for the first time ever, I can appreciate Edgar Allan Poe.  I've learnt quite a bit from her.  It's a saturday morning class, and probably my favourite right now!!  Great professor!
Our Saturday class gave her flowers on the last day of term--that should tell you something.

An amazing prof. She truly cares, and is fun to be around. There's truly almost no negatives -- she even justifies the mandatory attendance (in quiz form -- which she herself admitted to being wary about) in a kind and lovely way.
I hated English in high school and really didn't want to take this course. Professor Graham made literature fun. She also cared about us and how we did in the course. Take this course.

Great Professor. Found classes a little bit boring, but she seemed to always poke fun during the entire 3 hours. Assignments were well spaced apart and exam was fairly straight-forward. Very Sincere Prof.
I was surprised that someone found Professor Graham's class boring. I had a Saturday morning essay writing class with her, and it was my favorite class all term. Great teacher, and I learned a lot.

Although I honestly found her lectures very boring and her methods of evaluation very ambiguous and at times somewhat unfair, she turned out to be the sincerest professor I've ever had.  She really does care about the welfare of students.  I emailed her about a problem & she called me long distance to see if everything was ok!

This prof was the best English teacher I've ever had. She was very funny, and also extremely helpful.  She made it clear that you would get out of the class what you put into it, and it was true. Take this class, even if its just to see how she will work a Simpsons reference into each lecture!

Lorrie is a great teacher. Funny as hell and understands real people. She's very interesting and gives a**** what other people have to say. In other words, it's not all about her, like most English teachers. I enjoyed her assignments and her exams. I now know how to write a proper essay.

BEST ENGLISH PROF EVER..Her three hours classes passed very quickly..Her essay topic were very very interesting and general that everyone would like to discuss them.She is funny and she considers her students as one of her children...She's an awesome prof..Take her class without a second thought!

Very caring about her students. She went back to school as an adult so she can understand what everyone is going through. Fair marker, yet strict. Excellent professor.

amazing prof, very interesting and easy to talk to, ive learnt a lot from this prof, more than just on an academic level, shes probably the best english prof at ottawa u.  :)
Lorrie is an exceptional teacher. Serious, yet funny. Not much else to say except that I now know how to write an essay, well.
